1
00:00:01,002 --> 00:00:03,625
[NARRATOR]
Alchemy... the science
of understanding,

2
00:00:03,625 --> 00:00:05,925
deconstructing, and
reconstructing matter;

3
00:00:05,925 --> 00:00:09,291
however, it is not
an all-powerful art.

4
00:00:09,291 --> 00:00:12,158
It is impossible to
create something out of nothing.

5
00:00:12,158 --> 00:00:13,858
If one wishes to
obtain something,

6
00:00:13,858 --> 00:00:16,358
something of equal
value must be given.

7
00:00:16,358 --> 00:00:18,858
This is the Law of
Equivalent Exchange--

8
00:00:18,858 --> 00:00:20,858
the basis of all alchemy.

9
00:00:20,858 --> 00:00:22,225
In accordance with this law,

10
00:00:22,225 --> 00:00:24,291
there is a taboo
among alchemists.

11
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:26,625
Human transmutation
is strictly forbidden.

12
00:00:26,625 --> 00:00:29,891
For what could equal
the value of a human soul?

13
00:02:04,391 --> 00:02:05,706
[NARRATOR]
Maes Hughes is dead...

14
00:02:05,706 --> 00:02:07,373
The military knows
little of his killers

15
00:02:07,373 --> 00:02:10,773
beyond the fact that they bore
mysterious Uroboros tattoos...

16
00:02:10,773 --> 00:02:12,339
Suspicious about
the circumstances

17
00:02:12,339 --> 00:02:13,473
surrounding his friend's death,

18
00:02:13,473 --> 00:02:16,506
Colonel Mustang began
asking questions of his own.

19
00:02:16,506 --> 00:02:17,939
He learned of a
possible conspiracy

20
00:02:17,939 --> 00:02:20,273
at the senior level
of military command,

21
00:02:20,273 --> 00:02:23,539
which only redoubled his resolve
to be promoted to Central.

22
00:02:23,539 --> 00:02:25,706
Meanwhile, anxious to
see their old teacher,

23
00:02:25,706 --> 00:02:27,706
Ed and Al continued
their journey southward

24
00:02:27,706 --> 00:02:29,206
with Winry in tow,

25
00:02:29,206 --> 00:02:31,806
unaware of the death of
Lieutenant Colonel Hughes.

26
00:02:37,639 --> 00:02:40,339
[WINRY]
Rush Valley!

27
00:02:40,339 --> 00:02:44,539
Automail! Automail! Automail!

28
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:45,939
[WINRY LAUGHS]

29
00:02:45,939 --> 00:02:48,339
I'm so happy!

30
00:02:48,339 --> 00:02:50,273
[WINRY GASPS]

31
00:02:50,273 --> 00:02:53,439
Look, it's the most
recent Gods model!

32
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:54,773
I never imagined
I would behold

33
00:02:54,773 --> 00:02:57,439
such a thing with
my very own eyes!

34
00:02:57,439 --> 00:02:59,806
[WINRY SQUEALS IN EXCITEMENT]

35
00:03:00,573 --> 00:03:02,906
[AL] Welcome to
the Holy Land of automail!

36
00:03:02,906 --> 00:03:04,539
This place is bustling.

37
00:03:04,539 --> 00:03:07,239
[ED] Ugh! Remind me again
why we let ourselves get

38
00:03:07,239 --> 00:03:10,806
dragged out into this heat to
look at a bunch of automail?

39
00:03:10,806 --> 00:03:12,839
We should've dropped
Winry off at the station

40
00:03:12,839 --> 00:03:14,939
and headed straight
on to Dublith.

41
00:03:14,939 --> 00:03:17,273
[ENGINEER A]
Hey kid, come back here a sec!

42
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:20,706
I've never seen an automail
model quite like this before!

43
00:03:20,706 --> 00:03:23,406
It really is unusual.
Everyone take a look!

44
00:03:23,406 --> 00:03:24,973
[CROWD GASPS]

45
00:03:24,973 --> 00:03:26,339
[ED]
Hey, stop that.

46
00:03:26,339 --> 00:03:27,273
Hey, hold on a second!

47
00:03:27,273 --> 00:03:28,839
Have you ever heard
of personal space?!

48
00:03:28,839 --> 00:03:32,673
Quit it! No, no!
Don't undo that! Ahhhhhhhhhh!

49
00:03:32,673 --> 00:03:34,839
Don't be so rude.
They just want a closer look.

50
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:37,239
Can I get a little
help here, Winry?!

51
00:03:37,773 --> 00:03:39,273
[ED] Jeez!

52
00:03:39,273 --> 00:03:43,673
This is why I steer clear
of automail engineers.

53
00:03:43,673 --> 00:03:44,606
Oh no.

54
00:03:44,606 --> 00:03:46,306
Something wrong, Ed?

55
00:03:46,306 --> 00:03:49,539
It's gone...

56
00:03:49,539 --> 00:03:51,273
[AL AND WINRY]
What didja lose?

57
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:53,939
Only the thing that proves
I'm a State Alchemist.

58
00:03:53,939 --> 00:03:55,806
My silver watch...

59
00:03:55,806 --> 00:03:56,339
...gone!

60
00:03:56,339 --> 00:03:58,206
[AL AND WINRY YELL]

61
00:03:58,206 --> 00:04:00,806
It sounds like you guys
had a run in with Paninya.

62
00:04:00,806 --> 00:04:01,906
Paninya?

63
00:04:01,906 --> 00:04:03,406
A pickpocket
around here

64
00:04:03,406 --> 00:04:05,406
who likes to
target tourists.

65
00:04:05,406 --> 00:04:07,739
Do you know how I can
track down this Paninya girl?

66
00:04:07,739 --> 00:04:09,839
She took something important!

67
00:04:10,839 --> 00:04:12,606
Let's see,
where is she again?

68
00:04:12,606 --> 00:04:15,539
I know what might
jog my memory...

69
00:04:15,539 --> 00:04:18,573
If only I could have just
one more look at that automail!

70
00:04:19,973 --> 00:04:23,306
The automail shop run by
an engineer named Dominic!

71
00:04:27,939 --> 00:04:29,906
Apparently this guy lives
deep in the mountains

72
00:04:29,906 --> 00:04:33,206
because he can find the highest
quality ore way out here.

73
00:04:33,206 --> 00:04:36,339
Are you absolutely sure we're
going in the right direction?

74
00:04:36,339 --> 00:04:39,406
'Cause those engineers
could've tricked us.

75
00:04:39,406 --> 00:04:40,806
What're you
complaining about?

76
00:04:40,806 --> 00:04:42,339
This is all your fault
for dragging us to

77
00:04:42,339 --> 00:04:44,439
that stupid automail
town in the first place.

78
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:45,273
[WINRY] My fault?!

79
00:04:45,273 --> 00:04:45,939
You're the one
who was dumb enough

80
00:04:45,939 --> 00:04:47,373
to let his watch get stolen!

81
00:04:47,373 --> 00:04:48,773
[ED]
Oh! Really?!

82
00:04:48,773 --> 00:04:49,939
[AL]
Um, hey, you guys...

83
00:04:49,939 --> 00:04:51,373
What, Al?!

84
00:04:51,373 --> 00:04:52,406
[AL]
Could that be her?

85
00:04:52,406 --> 00:04:53,673
[ED AND WINRY] Huh...?

86
00:05:02,306 --> 00:05:04,939
Ha! Ha! I've got you now!

87
00:05:05,706 --> 00:05:06,773
[PANINYA GASPS]

88
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:23,939
I'd like my watch back.

89
00:05:23,939 --> 00:05:26,839
That was awesome!
How'd you do that, mister?

90
00:05:26,839 --> 00:05:29,306
I'm an alchemist... Want more?

91
00:05:34,339 --> 00:05:35,806
Wow! So cool!

92
00:05:35,806 --> 00:05:37,806
[ED GRUNTS]

93
00:05:37,806 --> 00:05:38,973
[ED]
Quit movin' around!

94
00:05:38,973 --> 00:05:40,239
[PANINYA]
What's the matter?

95
00:05:40,239 --> 00:05:41,839
Can't catch
a little girl?

96
00:05:44,306 --> 00:05:45,939
[AL]
I've been waiting for you.

97
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:49,506
Huh...?

98
00:05:54,873 --> 00:05:56,806
[WINRY]
Nicely done, Al.

99
00:05:56,806 --> 00:05:59,739
Now... Why don't you
hand it over? My watch--

100
00:06:01,573 --> 00:06:03,273
[AL AND ED GASP]

101
00:06:03,273 --> 00:06:05,273
Come on, you can't
be too surprised...

102
00:06:05,273 --> 00:06:07,273
You've seen the
town, haven't you?

103
00:06:07,273 --> 00:06:08,406
Oh, and...

104
00:06:08,406 --> 00:06:09,673
[AL AND ED SCREAM]

105
00:06:09,673 --> 00:06:11,906
My other leg's got a one
point five inch cannon.

106
00:06:11,906 --> 00:06:13,806
What do you think of that?

107
00:06:13,806 --> 00:06:14,773
Come back!

108
00:06:14,773 --> 00:06:17,539
No way! Why don't we
see if you can catch me?

109
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:21,939
Well now,
how do ya like that?

110
00:06:21,939 --> 00:06:23,673
That wasn't so hard.

111
00:06:23,673 --> 00:06:24,973
[ED]
Nice work, Winry!

112
00:06:24,973 --> 00:06:27,473
And now don't let her get away!

113
00:06:27,473 --> 00:06:29,806
[WINRY]
No way I'm letting her go!

114
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:31,539
Not quite yet, anyway...

115
00:06:31,539 --> 00:06:34,273
Not until I've had a closer
look at that automail!

116
00:06:34,273 --> 00:06:36,573
[AL AND ED YELL]

117
00:06:37,973 --> 00:06:39,806
Oh, hello there, Paninya.

118
00:06:41,306 --> 00:06:42,406
[SATERA]
Friends of yours?

119
00:06:42,406 --> 00:06:44,373
[PANINYA]
Not really...

120
00:06:48,606 --> 00:06:50,373
[WINRY SQUEALS IN EXCITEMENT]

121
00:06:50,373 --> 00:06:52,506
[WINRY] I've never seen
craftsmanship like this before!

122
00:06:52,506 --> 00:06:53,539
It has an advanced suspension,

123
00:06:53,539 --> 00:06:55,639
and would you look
at this balance!

124
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:57,739
The design of this piece
is truly a work of art!

125
00:06:57,739 --> 00:06:59,306
It's incredible!

126
00:06:59,306 --> 00:07:00,473
Um...

127
00:07:00,473 --> 00:07:02,539
[ED] Do you think we could
have a talk about my watch?

128
00:07:02,539 --> 00:07:04,306
[AL]
It's no use brother.

129
00:07:04,873 --> 00:07:06,939
The work you've done
is simply fantastic.

130
00:07:06,939 --> 00:07:08,573
You're a
wonderful engineer!

131
00:07:08,573 --> 00:07:10,306
Oh, no, don't
look at me miss.

132
00:07:10,306 --> 00:07:12,273
I wasn't the one
who made them.

133
00:07:12,273 --> 00:07:13,806
[DOMINIC] I am.

134
00:07:17,973 --> 00:07:19,239
Huh...?

135
00:07:19,239 --> 00:07:21,273
[METALLIC SOUND]

136
00:07:21,273 --> 00:07:22,873
This arm seems a bit heavy.

137
00:07:22,873 --> 00:07:24,973
Yes, I guess it is.

138
00:07:24,973 --> 00:07:27,673
You want to be more careful
not to strain your outfit-ee.

139
00:07:27,673 --> 00:07:29,906
That could be the reason
why his growth is stunted.

140
00:07:29,906 --> 00:07:31,639
[ED]
Hey, Shut up!

141
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:32,806
[ED GASPS]

142
00:07:32,806 --> 00:07:34,773
Wait, are you telling me that
if my automail was lighter,

143
00:07:34,773 --> 00:07:36,506
I'd grow taller than this?

144
00:07:36,506 --> 00:07:38,773
It is a possibility.

145
00:07:38,773 --> 00:07:41,339
Wow, Brother,
you're so big!

146
00:07:41,339 --> 00:07:42,906
You've grown
so tall!

147
00:07:42,906 --> 00:07:45,439
Next to me,
you guys sure look small.

148
00:07:46,839 --> 00:07:49,339
Right!
That settles it.

149
00:07:49,339 --> 00:07:50,773
Mister Dominic!

150
00:07:50,773 --> 00:07:52,273
Huh...?

151
00:07:52,273 --> 00:07:54,806
I beg you...
Make me your apprentice!

152
00:07:54,806 --> 00:07:56,539
Not a chance, girl.

153
00:07:57,806 --> 00:07:59,973
Maybe you'd like more
time to consider the idea?

154
00:07:59,973 --> 00:08:02,606
No need.
I don't take on apprentices.

155
00:08:02,606 --> 00:08:04,273
I understand,
but maybe...

156
00:08:04,273 --> 00:08:05,773
you could take time out
of your busy schedule

157
00:08:05,773 --> 00:08:08,906
to teach her how to make
automail to make me taller?

158
00:08:08,906 --> 00:08:10,406
Can it, ya little flea.

159
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:11,473
[ED GASPS]

160
00:08:17,906 --> 00:08:19,339
Sorry about that...

161
00:08:19,339 --> 00:08:22,606
My old man can
be pretty stubborn.

162
00:08:25,183 --> 00:08:28,350
[RAIN POURS]

163
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:31,350
A little flea...
A little flea...

164
00:08:31,350 --> 00:08:33,150
He called me a flea!

165
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:34,150
[AL]
Hmm...?

166
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:41,050
[AL] Excuse me, but
are you having a baby?

167
00:08:41,050 --> 00:08:42,817
Why, yes I am.

168
00:08:42,817 --> 00:08:43,817
[AL] Do you think...

169
00:08:43,817 --> 00:08:45,917
Would it be all right
if I touched your tummy?

170
00:08:45,917 --> 00:08:47,850
Heh...
Go right ahead.

171
00:08:58,850 --> 00:09:04,017
[HEARTBEAT SOUND]

172
00:09:08,417 --> 00:09:10,950
[ED] It's like there's
a miracle in your stomach.

173
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:13,817
[AL] Yeah... we were inside
Mom's tummy like this

174
00:09:13,817 --> 00:09:15,850
once upon a time too.

175
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:18,517
[SATERA WINCES IN PAIN]

176
00:09:18,517 --> 00:09:20,083
[ED]
Are you okay?

177
00:09:20,083 --> 00:09:22,083
[SATERA] Y-Yes.

178
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:24,883
[RAIN POURS]

179
00:09:24,883 --> 00:09:27,183
[PANINYA GRUNTS]

180
00:09:27,183 --> 00:09:28,450
Whenever it pours
down like this,

181
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:30,250
my stumps
always get achy.

182
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:32,817
If you don't mind me
asking, what happened?

183
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:38,183
[PANINYA]
I was in a train accident
when I was a kid...

184
00:09:38,183 --> 00:09:40,250
It killed my parents.

185
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:43,950
I wound up losing both
my legs in the wreck.

186
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,517
I couldn't even walk anymore...

187
00:09:45,517 --> 00:09:47,250
...and I had nowhere to go.

188
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:51,517
It felt like my entire world
had come crashing down.

189
00:09:51,517 --> 00:09:53,150
That's when I met
Mister Dominic,

190
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:55,483
and everything
changed completely.

191
00:10:08,017 --> 00:10:09,183
You look like
the most miserable,

192
00:10:09,183 --> 00:10:11,817
pathetic girl in
the entire world.

193
00:10:11,817 --> 00:10:13,883
Nothing annoys me more
than mopers like you.

194
00:10:13,883 --> 00:10:17,317
[YOUNG PANINYA]
Let me go, you mean
old man! Put me down!

195
00:10:17,317 --> 00:10:19,350
He said I had eyes
like a dead person.

196
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:21,017
Probably not far off.

197
00:10:21,017 --> 00:10:23,917
I'm sure I really
did look miserable.

198
00:10:23,917 --> 00:10:27,083
So, without anyone
ever asking my opinion...

199
00:10:27,083 --> 00:10:30,217
I was outfitted
with automail legs.

200
00:10:30,217 --> 00:10:32,750
The surgery and
rehabilitation were painful--

201
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:35,417
by far the hardest
thing I've ever done.

202
00:10:35,417 --> 00:10:36,883
But then...

203
00:10:38,283 --> 00:10:43,217
Soon enough I was back up
on two legs, and I was so happy!

204
00:10:43,217 --> 00:10:46,750
All thanks to him...

205
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:50,517
Mister Dominic...
I owe him everything.

206
00:10:50,517 --> 00:10:51,950
I'm gonna pay
him back somehow,

207
00:10:51,950 --> 00:10:53,950
even if it takes
me my whole life!

208
00:10:53,950 --> 00:10:56,383
Of course, he's never willing
to take any money from me,

209
00:10:56,383 --> 00:10:59,283
so that makes it
a bit more difficult.

210
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:01,283
That's why
you're a thief?

211
00:11:01,283 --> 00:11:02,383
If you're so
grateful to him,

212
00:11:02,383 --> 00:11:05,950
you should clean up your act
and stop picking pockets!

213
00:11:05,950 --> 00:11:07,917
Mr. Dominic gave
you these legs

214
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:10,117
out of a selfless
act of good will.

215
00:11:10,117 --> 00:11:11,483
So if you really
wanna pay him back,

216
00:11:11,483 --> 00:11:14,950
use that act
as an example!

217
00:11:14,950 --> 00:11:17,083
Instead of stealing trinkets
from hapless tourists,

218
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:20,050
stand strong on those two legs
that he made for you...

219
00:11:20,050 --> 00:11:22,083
Stand up and get to work!

220
00:11:24,450 --> 00:11:26,217
Mr. Dominic would
respect you more

221
00:11:26,217 --> 00:11:28,750
for doing that
than for stealing.

222
00:11:29,883 --> 00:11:32,250
Probably...

223
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:34,950
You know what,
you're right!

224
00:11:34,950 --> 00:11:38,950
[PANINYA]
From now on, I'll work honestly
to pay him back myself!

225
00:11:38,950 --> 00:11:39,917
So...

226
00:11:39,917 --> 00:11:42,017
...I should probably
give this thing back.

227
00:11:42,017 --> 00:11:43,183
[WINRY]
Mm-Hmm...

228
00:11:44,950 --> 00:11:46,350
Hey...
What... Uh-oh...

229
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:48,517
I think I may have
broken it or something...

230
00:11:48,517 --> 00:11:50,350
Can't get it to open.

231
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:51,717
Let me see.

232
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,783
No, don't worry,
it wasn't you...

233
00:11:54,783 --> 00:11:56,483
It's been sealed
up using alchemy.

234
00:11:56,483 --> 00:11:57,883
Why would he do that?

235
00:11:57,883 --> 00:12:00,150
I think I have
a pretty good idea why.

236
00:12:01,517 --> 00:12:04,983
Something's in here he's too
embarrassed to let anyone see.

237
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:08,150
Open!

238
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:11,917
Now... let's have a little
look at what Ed was hiding.

239
00:12:14,850 --> 00:12:20,083
[PANINYA] "Don't forget...
October 3rd... year eleven."

240
00:12:20,083 --> 00:12:21,417
A date?

241
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:26,150
Here... You should
give this back to Ed.

242
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:28,250
What is it, Winry?

243
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,017
Nothing...

244
00:12:30,017 --> 00:12:32,950
I'm going to ask Mr. Dominic
to apprentice me again.

245
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:35,483
[RAIN POURS]

246
00:12:35,483 --> 00:12:37,083
[KNOCKING]

247
00:12:37,083 --> 00:12:39,383
[FOOTSTEPS]

248
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:42,317
[ED BREATHES HEAVILY]

249
00:12:42,317 --> 00:12:43,350
[WINRY]
What's wrong?

250
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:45,417
The... the ba--

251
00:12:45,417 --> 00:12:46,350
The bay?

252
00:12:46,350 --> 00:12:48,450
[ED MUMBLES]

253
00:12:48,450 --> 00:12:50,450
A bay is a type of horse.
What about it?

254
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:52,017
The... the...

255
00:12:52,017 --> 00:12:54,850
The baby's coming!
The baby's coming!

256
00:12:56,917 --> 00:12:59,283
[WINRY SCREAMS]

257
00:12:59,283 --> 00:13:01,317
[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.

258
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:06,933
[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.

259
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,900
[LIGHTNING]

260
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:11,233
In a storm like this,
we can't get her

261
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:12,966
to the hospital in town.

262
00:13:12,966 --> 00:13:15,466
I'll fetch the
doctor myself.

263
00:13:15,466 --> 00:13:18,266
[HORSE GALLOPS]

264
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:21,300
[RIDEL] Pop will be right
back with a doctor...

265
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,033
Just hang on a little
longer for me... okay?

266
00:13:24,033 --> 00:13:25,433
There's no
hanging on here.

267
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:27,300
It'll come whenever
it's ready to.

268
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:28,333
[SATERA YELLS]

269
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:30,866
What's the matter, hon?

270
00:13:30,866 --> 00:13:32,533
[SATERA MUMBLES]

271
00:13:32,533 --> 00:13:33,204
Huh?

272
00:13:33,204 --> 00:13:35,866
[SATERA MUMBLES]

273
00:13:35,866 --> 00:13:37,366
Uh... sorry, one
more time...?

274
00:13:37,366 --> 00:13:40,266
I couldn't
hear that.

275
00:13:40,266 --> 00:13:42,466
I said it's coming!

276
00:13:42,466 --> 00:13:45,133
[EVERYONE YELLS]

277
00:13:45,133 --> 00:13:45,933
It's coming?!

278
00:13:45,933 --> 00:13:47,533
What do we do?
The doctor's not here!

279
00:13:47,533 --> 00:13:51,866
[EVERYONE YELLS WORRIEDLY]

280
00:13:51,866 --> 00:13:54,200
We're just going
to have to do it.

281
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,833
Have to do what?

282
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:58,133
Deliver it.

283
00:13:58,133 --> 00:14:00,000
[EVERYONE YELLS]

284
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:04,000
So... so you've seen a baby
being delivered before?

285
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,600
No, I... I haven't...

286
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:08,833
But we don't have any
other options here.

287
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,866
[WINRY]
I need everyone's help.

288
00:14:10,866 --> 00:14:12,833
We are going to do this!

289
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,966
Ed and Al, go and get me
some boiling water!

290
00:14:15,966 --> 00:14:16,933
- Right!
- Sure, Winry!

291
00:14:16,933 --> 00:14:18,500
Paninya, go find some towels.

292
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,233
And hurry!

293
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:20,200
Roger!

294
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:22,100
Mr. Ridel, do you have
any rubbing alcohol

295
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:23,833
we can use
for disinfectant?

296
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:26,333
I think we have some
in the store room.

297
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:27,600
[WINRY]
Oh, and some ice chips!

298
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,233
We'll put them by
Mrs. Satera's bedside.

299
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:36,900
Uh... are we sure your
friend can handle this?

300
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,100
Winry comes from
a family of doctors...

301
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:41,900
She grew up reading
medical textbooks

302
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:45,233
instead of picture books
like most kids her age.

303
00:14:45,233 --> 00:14:46,333
That's all
well and good,

304
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:49,100
but it isn't exactly the
same as a medical degree!

305
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,433
[ED] Well it's clear
that she at least

306
00:14:50,433 --> 00:14:52,333
vaguely remembers some of it.

307
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:53,900
[RIDEL]
Some of it!

308
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,333
Right now the only
choice we have is to

309
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:58,366
defer to her knowledge and
the sheer force of her nerve.

310
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:01,866
[RAIN POURS]

311
00:15:01,866 --> 00:15:03,833
[HORSE GALLOPS]

312
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:09,100
[WINRY] Boiling water...
disinfectant... towels...

313
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:12,466
And what else was there...?
Remember it now...

314
00:15:12,466 --> 00:15:14,500
[ED]
Winry...

315
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,300
[EVERYONE]
You can do this!

316
00:15:20,266 --> 00:15:22,366
[WINRY]
Paninya... give me
a hand in here.

317
00:15:22,366 --> 00:15:24,433
Sure...
you got it.

318
00:15:25,266 --> 00:15:26,833
[DOOR CREAKS CLOSED]

319
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:34,800
[AL] Brother...

320
00:15:36,133 --> 00:15:41,033
Now, when it really counts...
I can't do anything.

321
00:15:43,866 --> 00:15:45,366
[SATERA] Ow!!

322
00:15:45,366 --> 00:15:49,600
Agh! I'm gonna die in here!

323
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:54,033
It hurts!
I can't take anymore!

324
00:15:54,033 --> 00:15:57,300
[SATERA YELLS IN PAIN]

325
00:15:57,300 --> 00:16:01,100
I know we're not
big believers in God...

326
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:05,033
But maybe he could
help us... this once.

327
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:06,600
[HORSE GALLOPS]

328
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:11,100
[SATERA YELLS IN PAIN]

329
00:16:18,866 --> 00:16:20,100
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

330
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:21,366
[AL] Brother!

331
00:16:21,366 --> 00:16:24,100
Wha... what...?

332
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,833
All... that blood.

333
00:16:26,833 --> 00:16:28,833
[PANINYA]
I can't do it anymore.

334
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:32,300
[WINRY BREATHES HEAVILY]

335
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:34,866
What's going on...? Hey!

336
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:46,366
[BABY CRIES]

337
00:16:46,366 --> 00:16:47,866
[RIDEL AND SATERA LAUGH]

338
00:16:47,866 --> 00:16:50,533
It... It's a baby!

339
00:16:50,533 --> 00:16:53,366
Hooray!

340
00:16:53,366 --> 00:16:56,100
[ED] Awesome!
It's a real, live baby!

341
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:58,866
Awesome! Awesome,
awesome, awesome!

342
00:16:58,866 --> 00:17:00,033
Really...?
Awesome?

343
00:17:00,033 --> 00:17:02,400
That's all you can
think of to describe this?

344
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,600
How else should
I describe it?

345
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,866
This is the birth
of a new life!

346
00:17:05,866 --> 00:17:07,200
[ED] Alchemists have
worked for centuries,

347
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:09,100
and we're still not
able to do that!

348
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:11,866
A person creating
another person...

349
00:17:11,866 --> 00:17:13,033
You gotta be
kidding me!

350
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:15,366
Now you're lumping in alchemy
with the miracle of birth?!

351
00:17:15,366 --> 00:17:18,100
An occupational hazard.
It's just the way I think.

352
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:19,200
[BABY CRIES]

353
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:23,000
Besides, Whatever you say,
it really is awesome...

354
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,433
People are awesome.

355
00:17:26,166 --> 00:17:29,133
All right... The baby's born,
and everything's good...

356
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:30,366
So do you think
there's anything else

357
00:17:30,366 --> 00:17:32,366
you're gonna
need me for now?

358
00:17:32,366 --> 00:17:34,066
Yeah, there is.

359
00:17:34,066 --> 00:17:37,066
Do you think you could...
pick me up please?

360
00:17:37,066 --> 00:17:37,866
Huh?

361
00:17:39,566 --> 00:17:40,933
[WINRY]
It's humiliating
to be carried

362
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:43,300
by a boy who's
smaller than I am.

363
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:45,400
I could easily
drop you, you know.

364
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,433
[WINRY] Ed...

365
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:48,966
Huh, what is it?

366
00:17:48,966 --> 00:17:50,300
[WINRY]
I saw it...

367
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:54,066
The engraving that's
inside your pocket watch...

368
00:17:54,066 --> 00:17:54,766
[WINRY YELLS]

369
00:17:54,766 --> 00:17:59,100
Ow, ow, ow.
That really hurt!

370
00:17:59,100 --> 00:18:01,166
[ED]
You forced it open?

371
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,366
Yeah. I'm so sorry.

372
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:15,100
[ED] You idiot.

373
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:16,200
[WINRY]
Yeah...

374
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:26,100
I haven't shown that
to anybody. Not even Al.

375
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:28,266
But why not, Ed?

376
00:18:28,266 --> 00:18:31,466
[ED] It's private.
An admonition to myself.

377
00:18:33,533 --> 00:18:35,966
I hate to admit
how weak I am...

378
00:18:35,966 --> 00:18:38,100
That I had to give what
happened that day substance,

379
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:40,500
and then carry it around
with me as a reminder.

380
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:42,833
[RAIN POURS]

381
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:48,100
Winry, why are
you doing that?

382
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:50,133
What are you crying for?

383
00:18:58,866 --> 00:19:02,400
Well... there's no turning
back for us now, brother.

384
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:09,566
[GLASS CRACKS]

385
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,466
[ED] What are you
crying for, Winry?

386
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,100
[WINRY]
You two won't cry...

387
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:28,166
Someone else should do it
for you, don't you think?

388
00:19:28,166 --> 00:19:29,866
Don't be an idiot.

389
00:19:32,166 --> 00:19:34,266
[ED] You should get
back to Resembool.

390
00:19:34,266 --> 00:19:35,433
You've been gone
a long time.

391
00:19:35,433 --> 00:19:37,266
Granny must be
lonesome without you.

392
00:19:37,266 --> 00:19:39,333
[WINRY]
No... I'm not leaving.

393
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:40,266
Why?

394
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:44,966
[WINRY] Seeing your
resolve inspired me.

395
00:19:44,966 --> 00:19:46,933
I wanna do more, Ed.

396
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:49,133
I can't just commit halfway.

397
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:50,366
Don't do anything...

398
00:19:50,366 --> 00:19:52,366
There's no need to
get more involved.

399
00:19:52,366 --> 00:19:53,300
Yes there is...

400
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:55,566
I want to hone my skills
so I'll be able to

401
00:19:55,566 --> 00:19:58,466
make you the finest quality
automail prosthetics.

402
00:19:58,466 --> 00:20:00,400
That way you can continue
your journey knowing

403
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:03,200
you're as strong
as you can be.

404
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,533
I'm going to try again.

405
00:20:04,533 --> 00:20:07,900
I'll ask Mr. Dominic to
make me his apprentice.

406
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,100
Okay.

407
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,866
Well then, good luck.

408
00:20:15,066 --> 00:20:18,500
[PANINYA]
Winry! Mr. Ridel said he
wanted to talk to you for a...

409
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:21,266
What's up?
Is there something wrong?

410
00:20:21,266 --> 00:20:22,966
Oh no, don't worry.
It's nothing...

411
00:20:22,966 --> 00:20:24,266
I'll be right
there, okay.

412
00:20:24,266 --> 00:20:25,566
Paninya...

413
00:20:25,566 --> 00:20:26,366
Hmm...?

414
00:20:26,366 --> 00:20:28,000
[LOUD THUD]

415
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,833
Hey! Ow...!
Why'd you go and do that?

416
00:20:30,833 --> 00:20:32,366
Quit whining,
you dirty pickpocket,

417
00:20:32,366 --> 00:20:34,366
and give me my
watch back right now!

418
00:20:34,366 --> 00:20:36,166
[PANINYA]
Didja have to hit me
with your right arm?

419
00:20:36,166 --> 00:20:39,266
[ED]
I can hit you again with
my left if you'd prefer!

420
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:44,966
Hello, there--
I'm your granddad!

421
00:20:44,966 --> 00:20:46,200
What a cutie!

422
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:48,000
That's sure
out of character.

423
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,300
Mother and baby both
look perfectly healthy...

424
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:52,933
It seems like the delivery
was handled expertly.

425
00:20:52,933 --> 00:20:54,966
Well done. Sometimes
even adults can't take

426
00:20:54,966 --> 00:20:56,833
being present at childbirth.

427
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:59,366
Oh, no...! We did what
we had to, that's all!

428
00:20:59,366 --> 00:21:00,533
[DOMINIC]
We are truly in your debt.

429
00:21:00,533 --> 00:21:05,866
What you did was amazing.
Especially you, young lady.

430
00:21:05,866 --> 00:21:07,600
Thank you.

431
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:10,366
Please, sir, there's really
no need to thank me...!

432
00:21:10,366 --> 00:21:12,800
Oh my goodness,
now you're going make me blush!

433
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:16,100
Maybe you could
make an exception

434
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:17,966
and take on
an apprentice?

435
00:21:17,966 --> 00:21:20,433
One has nothing
to do with the other.

436
00:21:20,433 --> 00:21:23,533
[DOMINIC] I don't take on
apprentices, and that's that.

437
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:25,766
But...

438
00:21:25,766 --> 00:21:27,833
If that's what
your heart's set on...

439
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,966
I can recommend you to
an accomplished engineer

440
00:21:29,966 --> 00:21:31,500
at the base of the mountain.

441
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:36,966
Pardon me... would it
be okay if I came by

442
00:21:36,966 --> 00:21:39,466
and watched
you work sometimes?

443
00:21:39,466 --> 00:21:42,433
[DOMINIC]
I won't stop you from
coming once in awhile...

444
00:21:42,433 --> 00:21:44,166
...to see my grandchild.

445
00:21:44,166 --> 00:21:46,166
Same goes for the tomboy.

446
00:21:48,466 --> 00:21:51,000
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

447
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,366
[ED] Move it, Al!
We've gotta hurry.

448
00:21:53,366 --> 00:21:54,300
If we miss this train,

449
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:57,333
there's not another
one for three days!

450
00:21:57,333 --> 00:21:59,966
Now you two
be careful!

451
00:21:59,966 --> 00:22:01,266
You too, Winry!

452
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:04,100
[ED] Thank you.

453
00:22:04,100 --> 00:22:06,400
And don't forget to call
Granny and keep her posted!

454
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:09,366
Oh please, like you're
really one to talk, Ed!

455
00:22:09,366 --> 00:22:11,600
And make sure to steal
that old man's techniques

456
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:13,400
so you'll have something
even better for me

457
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:15,800
the next time I see you, okay?

458
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:24,500
Well, that's it.
They're gone.

459
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:26,100
They'll be back.

460
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:27,066
Huh...?

461
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,433
[NARRATOR]
The brothers arrive in Dublith
to visit their old teacher...

462
00:24:08,433 --> 00:24:10,166
While there, they
remember the time

463
00:24:10,166 --> 00:24:12,900
they spent in training
as young boys...

464
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:16,433
when they took their
first step toward the truth.

465
00:24:16,433 --> 00:24:20,433
Next time on Fullmetal
Alchemist: Brotherhood.

466
00:24:20,433 --> 00:24:22,166
Episode 12:

467
00:24:22,166 --> 00:24:26,333
"One is All, All is One."

468
00:24:26,333 --> 00:24:28,533
Afraid of the
possible consequences...

469
00:24:28,533 --> 00:24:31,833
...the Elric brothers
are hesitant to speak.

